TfL has some of the most iconic and valuable assets in London with the majority of its property portfolio in the heart of the city.

Previously, TfL sold assets and properties it no longer needed. But it says it has recently decided to retain and invest in its number of sites to generate profit. 

It has already started using some of the stations in this way, with space under Clapham North Tube now used by herb farmers.

It has also introduced a collection of pop-up shops at some stations, while Argos launched its first underground store at London's Cannon Street Tube station last year.

